Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating
whites from greens.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, scallion whites,
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Mediterranean spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@water{1%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Form mixture into 8 1 1/2-inch
meatballs.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Place meatballs on a #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack until browned and
cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Trim and quarter
@mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); thinly slice into
quarter-moons. Pick and roughly chop @dill{1/4%ounce}(fronds picked and
roughly chopped). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, cucumber, scallion greens, a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{6%tablespoon} with as much dill and
lemon zest as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @pita bread{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30-40%seconds}; halve crosswise.

Fill pitas with meatballs and salad. Drizzle with yogurt sauce. Divide
between plates and serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> To help prevent sticking, lightly oil baking sheet or coat with nonstick
> cooking spray first.
> Cut your meatballs in half for easier pita stuffing.